    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix cpack_256 rounding issue in DFT processing\n\n### Summary\nThe `cpack_256` function in the DFT library was producing incorrect results due to improper rounding when converting from 32-bit to 16-bit fixed-point values. This caused unexpected behavior in FFT/IFFT operations.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/TOOLS/oai_dfts.c`: Added proper rounding to both `cpack` and `cpack_256` functions\n- Added rounding constant (2^14) before right shift operations to improve accuracy\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen running DFT operations with certain input values, the output showed significant quantization errors compared to expected mathematical results. The issue was particularly noticeable in high-precision signal processing scenarios where truncation errors accumulated.\n\nUsers reported that calling `cpack_256()` with identical inputs to the 128-bit `cpack()` function produced different outputs, with `cpack_256` showing consistently lower accuracy due to the missing rounding step.\n\n"
}